sub_title: PhD in Geography - MA & BA in Geography
summary:
As a postdoctoral researcher in Geography with a focus on territorial management and public policies, my expertise lies in promoting sustainability and resilience in the face of climate, political, and land-use changes caused by large corporations in South America. I am particularly dedicated to supporting local communities in Argentina.

With visiting positions in the Netherlands, Austria, and Spain, I bring an interdisciplinary and participatory approach that brings together community, private, public, and research actors to achieve local development. I believe that collaboration is key to achieving positive change in the face of complex challenges.

My passion for agroecology stems from my recognition of its potential as a key science for working with nature to understand socio-ecological processes and improve the environmental quality of degraded areas. I am committed to promoting sustainable practices and developing innovative solutions that empower local communities and protect our planet for future generations.
